hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: In tens, please (ten pound notes) comfort pharmacy flushing “I think increasingly what makes our band work, we have to go do all these crazy projects, these sort of edgy, left-field projects because it’s what keeps us alive,” Ulrich said. “Making records is great and we love it and we appreciate the fact that we can make records ... but there’s also a familiarity to it. And you have a dynamic in the band of four personalities and they’re really curious and into different things and just kind of ready for whatever.”
